        <briefdescription>
<para>Square-clip a complex sample. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Clips the real and imaginary parts independently to &amp;#91;-lin, lin&amp;#93; — a square region in the IQ plane, not a circular magnitude limit.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>y</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Input sample. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>lin</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Per-component clip threshold (linear amplitude, &gt;= 0). </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>Sample with each component limited to &amp;#91;-lin, lin&amp;#93;. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
